verse.lines:
{lang-eng}Behold! A spotless Victim dies,
My surety on the tree;
The Lamb of God, the Sacrifice,
He gave Himself for me!{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Whatever curse was mine, He bore;
The wormwood and the gall,
There, in that lone mysterious hour,
My cup—He drained it all!{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Thine is the joy, but yet ‘tis mine.
‘Tis ours as one with Thee;
My joy flows from that grief of Thine;
Thy death brings life to me!{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}And while the ages roll along,
This shall my glory be;
And this the new and endless song,
Thy love to us—to me!{/lang-eng}
